Hi, thanks for using Weex. Please follow the [Bug Report Guidelines](http://weex-project.io/bug-report-guidelines.html) to file issue of Weex. A good bug report should include the following information:

### Description

> The overview or description of a bug report is to explain the bug in detail.

### Example to Reproduce

> Offer an example on http://dotwe.org/ to reproduce the bug.

### Environment

> The environment to reproduce this bug, such as **Weex Version** and the **Device Information**. You can get those information throw [this example](http://dotwe.org/vue/1dea64f527db3fd109c0fb682d41c14f).

### Steps to Reproduce

> The aim to provide the reproducible steps is to enable developers to reproduce the bug in their own environment.
